Explanation:

We iterate through numbers from 1 to n (inclusive). For each number, we check if it is divisible by k and has k digits. If it meets both conditions, we increment the count. The time complexity is O(n) because we iterate through all numbers from 1 to n. The space complexity is O(1) because we only use a constant amount of space for the count variable. The energy implications are low because the algorithm only performs simple arithmetic operations and does not require any complex calculations or data structures.

